# Legend and Technical Details
legend: |md
  **Legend:** ✓ = Test passes
  This matrix tests all 16×16 combinations of:
  - **Alignment offset (0-15):** Starting position within 16-byte aligned block
  - **String length (0-16):** Number of bytes before null terminator
  Critical boundary cases:
  - len=0: Empty string (null at position 0)
  - len=4: Exact float width
  - len=8: Half AVX width  
  - len=15: One byte below SSE vector width
  - len=16: Exact SSE vector width (one full chunk)
  Alignment edge cases:
  - align=0: Already aligned (no prologue needed)
  - align=15: Maximum prologue (15 scalar bytes)
| {near: bottom-center}

style: {
  fill: white
  stroke: "#666666"
}